cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the generation of high fidelity images. It also involves the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper addresses the challenges of encoding vast previous context and learning a distribution that preserves both global semantic coherence and exactness of detail, which could place it in the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of multidimensional upscaling, which could suggest that it belongs to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
